Barclays Africa said on Thursday it would no longer consider reappointing troubled KPMG as one of its external auditors.
“Ongoing and more recent developments were evaluated by the board, which decided that it is no longer able to support the re-appointment of KPMG Inc.,” the company said in a statement, alluding to controversies surrounding the auditing firm including its release of a discredited report about a unit at the national revenue service, Sars.
In a statement, KPMG said it was disappointed by the decision taken by Barclays Africa, but fully accept it.
